<aside id="topic1">
<p>Flowers are important for many reasons, including:<br>
Reproduction: Flowers are the reproductive organs of flowering plants.<br> They attract pollinators, which help plants reproduce and form the next generation. 
<br>Food source: Flowers provide nectar and pollen for many animals, <br>including bees, beetles, birds, and bats<br>
Biodiversity: Flowers add color, texture, and biodiversity to gardens and environments. <br>
Genetic diversity: Pollination contributes to genetic diversity within plant populations, which is key to the adaptability and survival of species. 
Ornamental value: Some flowers are bright colored and have strong fragrance, so they can be used for decorative purposes. 
Medicine: Some flowers, like passionflower and milk thistle, have medicinal properties. 
</p>
</aside>
